# Artifact Registry Module

This Terraform module creates a Google Artifact Registry repository with optional cleanup policies, CMEK, labels, and IAM bindings.

## Features

- ✅ **Repository Creation** - Create Artifact Registry repository in a chosen location
- ✅ **Multiple Formats** - Supports Docker, Maven, NPM, Python, APT, YUM, GO, KFP
- ✅ **Repository Modes** - Standard, Remote, or Virtual repository modes
- ✅ **Cleanup Policies** - Configure retention and cleanup behavior
- ✅ **CMEK Support** - Optional customer-managed encryption key
- ✅ **IAM Bindings** - Readers, writers, and admins
- ✅ **Tagging/Labels** - Environment and custom labels

## Usage

### Call from another repository

Point `source` at this repo and the path under it (`//Gcp/ArtifactRegistry`). Pin **`ref` to a tag or commit** in production, not a branch that can change.

```hcl
module "artifact_registry" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Gcp/ArtifactRegistry?ref=main"
  # Use ?ref=v1.0.0 (or a commit SHA) once you tag releases
  # ...same inputs as in Basic Usage below
}
```

The **root** module where you call this must configure the **Google** provider and authentication. This module only declares it needs `hashicorp/google`.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    google = {
      source  = "hashicorp/google"
      version = ">= 6.47.0, < 8.0.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "google" {
  project = var.project_id
  region  = var.location
}
```

### Basic Usage

```hcl
module "artifact_registry" {
  source = "../../modules/Gcp/ArtifactRegistry"

  project_id    = "my-project-id"
  location      = "us-central1"
  repository_id = "app-images"
  format        = "DOCKER"

  readers = [
    "serviceAccount:viewer@my-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  ]

  writers = [
    "serviceAccount:builder@my-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
  ]
}
```

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| `project_id` | GCP project ID | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `location` | Repository location | `string` | `"us-central1"` | no |
| `repository_id` | Artifact Registry repository ID | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `description` | Repository description | `string` | `"Managed by Terraform"` | no |
| `format` | Repository package format | `string` | `"DOCKER"` | no |
| `mode` | Repository mode | `string` | `"STANDARD_REPOSITORY"` | no |
| `immutable_tags` | Docker tag immutability | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `cleanup_policy_dry_run` | Run cleanup in dry-run mode | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `cleanup_policies` | Cleanup policy map | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `kms_key_name` | CMEK key name | `string` | `null` | no |
| `readers` | IAM members with reader role | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `writers` | IAM members with writer role | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `admins` | IAM members with admin role | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `labels` | Additional labels | `map(string)` | `{}` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `repository_id` | Artifact Registry repository ID |
| `repository_name` | Full repository resource name |
| `repository_format` | Repository package format |
| `repository_location` | Repository location |
| `summary` | High-level module summary |
| `connection_info` | Basic docker auth/image prefix helper |

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.3.0 |
| google | >= 6.47.0, < 8.0.0 |

## Providers

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| google | >= 6.47.0, < 8.0.0 |
